
[1]audience

   AUD'IENCE, n.

   1. The act of hearing, or attending to sounds.

   His bold discourse had audience.

   2. Admittance to a hearing; public reception to an interview; a
   ceremony observed in courts, or by official characters, when
   ambassadors or applicants to men in office are permitted to appear and
   state their business in person.

   3. An auditory; an assembly of hearers.

   4. In the Spanish dominions, a court; as the audience of Seville, which
   is a court of oyer and terminer; and the audience pretorial, in the
   Indies, which is a high court of judicature. The word in Spain also
   signifies certain law-officers, appointed to institute a judicial
   inquiry.

   5. In England, a court held by the arch-bishop of Canterbury, on the
   subject of consecrations, elections, institutions, marriages, &c.
